# shadcn/ui Component Guidelines

## Select Component Best Practices

- When using the Select component, avoid using both `value` and `defaultValue` props together as it can cause conflicts
- For controlled components, use only the `value` prop
- Display selected values in `SelectValue` by directly rendering the label, not just using placeholder
- Always handle the `onValueChange` event to update the parent state
- Use TypeScript generics when the select options can have different value types 

## Select Component Value Handling

- When using shadcn/ui Select component, ensure proper value synchronization between the Select and SelectValue components
- SelectValue should include both defaultValue and children props for proper display
- For controlled components, pass the selected value's id to both Select and SelectValue
- Keep the label display logic inside SelectValue for proper UI updates
- Always handle both the value and display text separately in shadcn/ui Select components 